##############################################

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGML.pl",
  "contextCurrency.pl",
  "PCCmacros.pl",
  "pccTables.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl",
);

##############################################

Context("Currency");
Context()->currency->addSymbol("dollars","dollar");
Context()->flags->set(trimTrailingZeros=>1);
Context()->operators->undefine('+','-');

do{
$rInit = random(10000,15000,1000);
$cInit = Currency($rInit);
$p1 = random(10,14,1)+random(1,9,1)/10;
$p2 = random(5,8,2)+random(1,9,1)/10;
$dp1 = $p1/100;
$dp2 = $p2/100;
$rFund1 = random(7500,9500,500);
$rFund2 = $rInit-$rFund1;
$cFund1 = Currency($rFund1);
$cFund2 = Currency($rFund2);

$rTotalInt = $rFund1*$dp1-$rFund2*$dp2;
} until ($rTotalInt > 0);

$cTotalInt = Currency($rTotalInt);

$sex = list_random('male','female');
$pronoun = 'he' if ($sex eq 'male');
$pronoun = 'she' if ($sex eq 'female');

$name = RandomName(sex=>$sex);


##############################################

TEXT(beginproblem());

BEGIN_PGML

[$name] invested a total of [`[$cInit]`] in two accounts. After a year, one account had _earned_ [`[$p1]%`], while the other account had _lost_ [`[$p2]%`]. In total, [$name] had a net gain of [`[$cTotalInt]`]. How much money did [$name] invest in each account?

    [$name] invested [__________]{$cFund1} in the account that grew by [`[$p1]%`] and [__________]{$cFund2} in the account that fell by [`[$p2]%`].

END_PGML

##############################################

$s1=$dp2*$rInit;
$s2=$dp1+$dp2;
$s3=$rTotalInt+$s1;

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_SOLUTION
$PAR
Let's let \(x\) represent the amount (in dollars) that $name had invested in the account with \($p1%\) gain. Then $pronoun  must have invested \($rInit -x\) dollars in the account with \($p2%\) loss.
$PAR
\{ucfirst($pronoun)\} gained \($dp1  x\) dollars from the first account, and lost \($dp2  ($rInit -x)\) dollars from the second account.
$PAR
Let's organize the quantities (rate, principal investment, and net gain/loss) for each of the two accounts into a table:

$PAR
\{ 
DataTable([[{data=>"",header=>"CH"},{data=>"Rate",header=>"CH"},{data=>" \(\times\)",header=>"CH"},{data=>"Principal",header=>"CH"},{data=>"\(=\)",header=>"CH"},{data=>"Net Gain",header=>"CH"},],
[{data=>"\(+$p1%\) Investment",header=>"RH"},"\($dp1\)","$SPACE","\(x\)","$SPACE","\($dp1 x\)"],
[{data=>"\(-$p2%\) Investment",header=>"RH"},"\(-$dp2\)","$SPACE","\($rInit-x\)","$SPACE","\(-$dp2($rInit-x)\)"],
], allcellcss=>"border:1px solid;padding:4pt;text-align:center;", caption => "Organize data with a table", captioncss =>"padding:4pt; text-decoration:none;");
\}  

$PAR

The table shows us that $name had a net gain of \($dp1 x-$dp2($rInit-x)\) from  the combination of the two accounts. The introduction tells us that $pronoun had a net gain of \($cTotalInt\). Now we can write an equation and then solve it:
$PAR

\[
\begin{aligned}
  $dp1  x - $dp2  ($rInit -x) & = $rTotalInt  \\
  $dp1  x +(- $dp2 ) ($rInit +(-x)) & = $rTotalInt  \\
  $dp1  x +(- $dp2 ) \cdot $rInit +(-$dp2 ) \cdot (-x) & = $rTotalInt  \\
  $dp1  x - $s1 +$dp2 x & = $rTotalInt  \\
  $s2  x - $s1  & = $rTotalInt  \\
  $s2  x - $s1 \mathbf{{}+$s1} & = $rTotalInt \mathbf{{}+$s1}  \\
  $s2 x          & = $s3  \\
  \frac{$s2 x}{$s2 } & = \frac{$s3 }{$s2 } \\
  x               & = $rFund1 
\end{aligned}
\]

$PAR
So $name invested \($cFund1 \) in the account with \($p1%\) gain, and $pronoun must have invested \($cInit -$cFund1\), or  \($cFund2 \) in the  account with \($p2%\) loss.
$PAR

END_SOLUTION

